 Delta State Governor, H.E Sen. Dr. Ifeanyi Arthur Okowa. Photo/Twitter/GovIfeanyiOkowa  Ukah stated this when the National Association of Proprietors of Private Schools (NAPPS), Delta State chapter visited him in his office, warning that the Inspectorate Department of the ministry would soon begin clampdown on private schools that are deviating from the norm. He explained that the decision was based on the abuse of provisional approvals earlier given whereby proprietors do nothing to improve standards in their schools after obtaining the approvals. He lamented the situation where private school owners do nothing to add value to what they had on the ground that guaranteed them the provisional approvals, saying the state government would no longer tolerate such acts. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .